Bias Mitigation & Fairness: How are you identifying and reducing potential AI bias (e.g., gender, regional, or linguistic bias)?
We reduce potential AI bias by using diverse synthetic and open-source data that represents different emergency scenarios, regions, and reporting styles. The system is tested with various text inputs and image conditions to ensure fair classification results. In addition, AI is only used as a support tool for emergency categorization, while the final response is based on predefined system rules to minimize biased or inaccurate decisions. 
We reduce visual bias by selecting training data that covers diverse geographical layouts and environmental states, such as varied lighting and weather conditions. For text processing, we incorporate a wide range of reporting styles to account for linguistic differences. Crucially, the AI only provides severity classification; final dispatch decisions are governed by predefined system rules to ensure fair and consistent emergency response across all ASEAN districts.
